  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways and deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon)</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1621861018074-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1621861018074-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1621861018074-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1621861018074-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1621861018074-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>onion</strong> <strong>wedges </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with<strong> half </strong>the <strong>green chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Blitz until finely chopped – this is your<strong> curry base</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>curry base</strong> with your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> curry powder </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1621861029824-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1621861029824-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1621861029824-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1621861029824-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1621861029824-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim the green stalk[s] off your<strong> aubergine[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and discard, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine</strong> and <strong>halved</strong> <strong>green beans</strong> to the pan</p><p>Mix everything together and cook for 1-2 min until the spices have coated the vegetables</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1621861038393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1621861038393-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1621861038393-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1621861038393-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1621861038393-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Add 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[455ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[595ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1621861053758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
